Doctors alarmed by burn victim numbers             Graham Kajilwa  04th Sep 2019 02:00:00 GMT +0300 Graham Kajilwa  04th Sep 2019 02:00:00 GMT +0300 Graham Kajilwa   Truphosa Gacheri participates in a discussion during a fire safety and burns awareness session at the Kenyatta National Hospital. The campaign, which started on Monday and runs till Friday, is intended to educate the public on prevention of fire outbreaks. Sensitisation activities will be held in Kibra, Mukuru kwa Njenga and in the central business district. [David Gichuru, Standard]  Truphosa Gacheri participates in a discussion during a fire safety and burns awareness session at the Kenyatta National Hospital. The campaign, which started on Monday and runs till Friday, is intended to educate the public on prevention of fire outbreaks. Sensitisation activities will be held in Kibra, Mukuru kwa Njenga and in the central business district. [David Gichuru, Standard] Truphosa Gacheri participates in a discussion during a fire safety and burns awareness session at the Kenyatta National Hospital. The campaign, which started on Monday and runs till Friday, is intended to educate the public on prevention of fire outbreaks. Sensitisation activities will be held in Kibra, Mukuru kwa Njenga and in the central business district. [David Gichuru, Standard] Truphosa Gacheri participates in a discussion during a fire safety and burns awareness session at the Kenyatta National Hospital. The campaign, which started on Monday and runs till Friday, is intended to educate the public on prevention of fire outbreaks. Sensitisation activities will be held in Kibra, Mukuru kwa Njenga and in the central business district.         For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper. For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper.   Awareness campaign                We are undertaking a survey to help us improve our content for you. This will only take 1 minute of your time, 